 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-bxi5","title":"Implement structured logging for HTML export pipeline","description":"## Overview
Add comprehensive structured logging throughout the HTML export pipeline to enable debugging, performance monitoring, and test verification.

## Logging Architecture

### Log Levels
- **TRACE**: Fine-grained details (each message rendered, byte counts)
- **DEBUG**: Component boundaries (entering/exiting functions, options)
- **INFO**: Major milestones (export started, encryption applied, file written)
- **WARN**: Recoverable issues (CDN fallback, long message truncated)
- **ERROR**: Failures that stop export

### Structured Fields
Every log entry includes:
```rust
#[derive(Serialize)]
struct ExportLogEntry {
    timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,
    level: Level,
    component: &str,        // "template", "encryption", "renderer", etc.
    operation: &str,        // "render_message", "encrypt_payload", etc.
    session_id: Option<&str>,
    duration_ms: Option<u64>,
    bytes_processed: Option<usize>,
    message: String,
    context: Option<serde_json::Value>,
}
```

## Component-Specific Logging

### Template Generation (template.rs)
```rust
info!(
    component = "template",
    operation = "generate",
    session_id = %session.id,
    message_count = session.messages.len(),
    "Starting HTML template generation"
);

debug!(
    component = "template",
    operation = "inline_css",
    bytes = css.len(),
    "Inlined critical CSS"
);

trace!(
    component = "template",
    operation = "inject_script",
    script_name = "theme_toggle",
    bytes = script.len(),
    "Injected inline script"
);
```

### Renderer (renderer.rs)
```rust
info!(
    component = "renderer",
    operation = "render_conversation",
    messages = conversation.messages.len(),
    agent = %conversation.agent_slug,
    "Beginning conversation render"
);

for (idx, msg) in messages.iter().enumerate() {
    trace!(
        component = "renderer",
        operation = "render_message",
        message_idx = idx,
        role = %msg.role,
        content_len = msg.content.len(),
        "Rendering message"
    );
}

debug!(
    component = "renderer",
    operation = "render_code_block",
    language = %lang,
    lines = code.lines().count(),
    "Rendered code block with syntax hints"
);
```

### Encryption (encryption.rs)
```rust
info!(
    component = "encryption",
    operation = "encrypt_payload",
    plaintext_bytes = plaintext.len(),
    iterations = config.pbkdf2_iterations,
    "Starting payload encryption"
);

debug!(
    component = "encryption",
    operation = "derive_key",
    duration_ms = elapsed.as_millis(),
    "Key derived via PBKDF2"
);

info!(
    component = "encryption",
    operation = "encrypt_complete",
    ciphertext_bytes = ciphertext.len(),
    duration_ms = total_elapsed.as_millis(),
    "Encryption complete"
);
```

### File Operations (filename.rs, file writing)
```rust
info!(
    component = "file",
    operation = "determine_path",
    downloads_dir = %downloads.display(),
    filename = %filename,
    "Determined output path"
);

debug!(
    component = "file",
    operation = "collision_check",
    attempts = attempt_count,
    final_path = %path.display(),
    "Resolved filename collision"
);

info!(
    component = "file",
    operation = "write_complete",
    path = %path.display(),
    bytes = bytes_written,
    duration_ms = elapsed.as_millis(),
    "HTML file written successfully"
);
```

## Test Logging Integration

### Test Log Capture
```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use tracing_test::traced_test;

    #[traced_test]
    #[test]
    fn test_export_logs_correctly() {
        let result = export_session(&session, &options);

        // Verify specific log entries
        assert!(logs_contain("Starting HTML template generation"));
        assert!(logs_contain("Encryption complete"));
        assert!(logs_contain("HTML file written successfully"));

        // Verify no errors
        assert!(!logs_contain("ERROR"));
    }
}
```

### E2E Test Log Verification
```rust
#[test]
fn test_export_full_pipeline_with_logging() {
    let subscriber = tracing_subscriber::fmt()
        .json()
        .with_test_writer()
        .finish();

    let _guard = tracing::subscriber::set_default(subscriber);

    let result = export_session(&session, &options);

    // Parse captured logs
    let logs: Vec<ExportLogEntry> = parse_test_logs();

    // Verify pipeline stages
    assert!(logs.iter().any(|l| l.operation == "generate"));
    assert!(logs.iter().any(|l| l.operation == "render_conversation"));
    assert!(logs.iter().any(|l| l.operation == "write_complete"));

    // Verify timing captured
    let write_log = logs.iter().find(|l| l.operation == "write_complete").unwrap();
    assert!(write_log.duration_ms.is_some());
    assert!(write_log.bytes_processed.is_some());
}
```

## Robot Mode Log Output
When --robot flag is used:
```json
{
    "success": true,
    "exported": { ... },
    "logs": [
        {"level": "info", "component": "template", "operation": "generate", "message": "..."},
        {"level": "debug", "component": "renderer", "operation": "render_message", "message": "..."}
    ]
}
```

With --verbose flag, include all log levels including TRACE.

## Performance Logging
```rust
// Wrap major operations with timing
let _span = tracing::info_span!(
    "export_session",
    session_id = %session.id,
    messages = session.messages.len()
).entered();

// Automatic duration on span drop
```

## Log Configuration
- Default: INFO level
- --verbose: DEBUG level
- --trace: TRACE level (very detailed)
- --quiet: WARN and above only
- --log-json: JSON formatted logs

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All major operations logged at appropriate levels
- [ ] Structured fields include timing and byte counts
- [ ] Tests can capture and verify log output
- [ ] Robot mode includes log array in JSON output
- [ ] No sensitive data (passwords) in logs
- [ ] Performance overhead < 1% of export time

