-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-fdowf","title":"[MEDIUM] reality-check: README semantic model-install claims contradict reality","description":"## Claim (README.md:203)
> **Manual install**: Place model files under your data directory (see below); cass will not auto-download.

## Reality (README.md:2453-2455 and actual CLI help)
\`cass models install\` DOES auto-download the model (~90 MB) from Hugging Face:

\`\`\`
\$ cass models install --help
Download and install the semantic search model
  --mirror <MIRROR>      Custom HTTP(S) mirror base URL for downloading
  --from-file <FROM_FILE> Install from local model directory (for air-gapped environments)
  -y, --yes              Skip confirmation prompt
\`\`\`

README line 2454 also describes the download path explicitly: \`cass models install # → Downloads from Hugging Face, verifies checksum\`.

Line 203 and line 2454 directly contradict each other.

## Secondary claim on same page
\`\`\`
cass models status --json
# → { \"installed\": true, \"model\": \"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\", \"size_bytes\": 91234567 }
