## Overview
Implement the `cass sources add` command for registering new remote sources,
including platform presets for common configurations.

## Implementation Details

### CLI Definition
In `src/cli.rs`:
```rust
#[derive(Parser)]
pub enum SourcesCommand {
    /// Add a new remote source
    Add {
        /// Source URL (e.g., ssh://user@host or just user@host)
        url: String,

        /// Friendly name for this source (becomes source_id)
        #[arg(long)]
        name: Option<String>,

        /// Use preset paths for platform (macos-defaults, linux-defaults)
        #[arg(long)]
        preset: Option<String>,

        /// Paths to sync (can be specified multiple times)
        #[arg(long = "path", short = 'p')]
        paths: Vec<String>,

        /// Skip connectivity test
        #[arg(long)]
        no_test: bool,
    },
    // ...
}
```

### Platform Presets
```rust
pub fn get_preset_paths(preset: &str) -> Result<Vec<String>, PresetError> {
    match preset {
        "macos-defaults" => Ok(vec![
            "~/.claude/projects".into(),
            "~/.codex/sessions".into(),
            "~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/globalStorage/...".into(),
            "~/Library/Application Support/com.openai.chat".into(),
            "~/.gemini/tmp".into(),
            "~/.pi/agent/sessions".into(),
            "~/.local/share/opencode".into(),
            "~/.continue/sessions".into(),
        ]),
        "linux-defaults" => Ok(vec![
            "~/.claude/projects".into(),
            "~/.codex/sessions".into(),
            "~/.config/Cursor/User/globalStorage/...".into(),
            "~/.gemini/tmp".into(),
            "~/.pi/agent/sessions".into(),
            "~/.local/share/opencode".into(),
            "~/.continue/sessions".into(),
        ]),
        _ => Err(PresetError::Unknown(preset.into())),
    }
}
```

### URL Parsing
```rust
fn parse_source_url(url: &str) -> Result<(String, String), SourceError> {
    let url = url.strip_prefix("ssh://").unwrap_or(url);

    if !url.contains('@') {
        return Err(SourceError::InvalidUrl("Missing username in URL".into()));
    }

    let (user, host) = url.split_once('@')
        .ok_or_else(|| SourceError::InvalidUrl("Invalid URL format".into()))?;

    Ok((user.to_string(), host.to_string()))
}
```

### Connectivity Test
```rust
async fn test_ssh_connectivity(host: &str) -> Result<(), SourceError> {
    let output = Command::new("ssh")
        .args(["-o", "ConnectTimeout=5", "-o", "BatchMode=yes", host, "echo", "ok"])
        .output()
        .await?;

    if !output.status.success() {
        let stderr = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stderr);
        return Err(SourceError::ConnectivityFailed(stderr.to_string()));
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

### Command Flow
```rust
async fn cmd_sources_add(args: &AddArgs) -> Result<(), CliError> {
    let (user, host) = parse_source_url(&args.url)?;

    // Generate source_id from hostname if not provided
    let source_id = args.name.clone().unwrap_or_else(|| {
        host.split('.').next().unwrap_or(&host).to_string()
    });

    // Get paths from preset or explicit args
    let paths = if let Some(preset) = &args.preset {
        get_preset_paths(preset)?
    } else if args.paths.is_empty() {
        // Prompt: "No paths specified. Use --preset or --path. Try --preset macos-defaults?"
        return Err(CliError::NoPaths);
    } else {
        args.paths.clone()
    };

    // Test connectivity
    if !args.no_test {
        println!("Testing SSH connectivity to {}...", host);
        test_ssh_connectivity(&format!("{}@{}", user, host)).await?;
        println!("✓ Connected successfully");
    }

    // Save to config
    let mut config = SourcesConfig::load()?;
    config.sources.push(SourceDefinition {
        name: source_id.clone(),
        source_type: SourceConnectionType::Ssh,
        host: Some(format!("{}@{}", user, host)),
        paths,
        ..Default::default()
    });
    config.save()?;

    println!("✓ Added source '{}'. Run 'cass sources sync' to fetch sessions.", source_id);
    Ok(())
}
```

